Project Title

Name Classification API

📌 Description

This is a RESTful backend API that classifies a given name by predicting its likely gender using an external API. The system processes the response, applies validation rules, and returns a structured JSON response.

The API also determines confidence levels based on probability and sample size, and handles errors gracefully.

🚀 Features
Accepts a name as input via query parameters
Fetches gender prediction from external API
Processes and formats response data
Computes confidence level (is_confident)
Returns standardized JSON responses
Handles multiple error scenarios
Includes CORS support for external access
Generates timestamps in ISO 8601 (UTC)
🛠️ Tech Stack
Backend: Node.js
Framework: Express.js
HTTP Client: Axios
Middleware: CORS
📂 Project Structure
project-folder/
│
├── node_modules/
├── server.js
├── package.json
├── README.md
⚙️ Installation & Setup
1. Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/Susan12-n/susan_Ntask0
cd your-repo
2. Install dependencies
npm install
3. Run the server
node app.js

Server will run on:

http://localhost:3000
🌐 API Endpoint
🔹 Classify Name
GET /api/classify?name={name}
✅ Example Request
http://localhost:3000/api/classify?name=John
✅ Success Response (200 OK)
{
  "status": "success",
  "data": {
    "name": "john",
    "gender": "male",
    "probability": 0.99,
    "sample_size": 12345,
    "is_confident": true
  },
  "processed_at": "2026-04-14T20:30:00Z"
}
❌ Error Responses
🔸 400 Bad Request

Missing or empty name:

{
  "status": "error",
  "message": "Missing or empty name parameter"
}
🔸 422 Unprocessable Entity

Invalid name type:

{
  "status": "error",
  "message": "name is not a string"
}
🔸 404 / No Prediction
{
  "status": "error",
  "message": "No prediction available for the provided name"
}
🔸 500 / 502 Server Error
{
  "status": "error",
  "message": "Server error"
}
🧠 Business Logic
✔ Data Transformation
Extract:
gender
probability
count
Rename:
count → sample_size
✔ Confidence Rule
is_confident = true IF:
- probability ≥ 0.7
AND
- sample_size ≥ 100
Otherwise false
✔ Timestamp
Generated on every request
Format: ISO 8601 (UTC)

Example:

2026-04-14T20:30:00Z
🔐 CORS Configuration

CORS is enabled to allow external systems (like grading scripts) to access the API.

app.use(cors());
🧪 Testing

You can test using:

Browser
Postman
Curl

Example:

curl http://localhost:3000/api/classify?name=Mary
